{
  "answer": "**\"Ajab waa'iz ki deen-daari hai ya Rabb\"**\n\nThis is the precise opening line (the first line of the poem, which doubles as the chapter title) in the transliteration variant of *Bang-E-Dara Part 1*, chapter 1.[^1]\n\nIn the English translation variant, it opens: \"What wondrous piety, for all to see,\".[^2]\n\n[^1]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 1*, ch. 1 (\"Ajab waa'iz ki deen-daari hai ya Rabb\"), [transliteration](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-1-55b25c/01-ajab-waaiz-ki-deen-daari-hai-ya-rabb/transliteration/).\n\n[^2]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 1*, ch. 1 (\"Ajab waa'iz ki deen-daari hai ya Rabb\"), [paragraph](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-1-55b25c/01-ajab-waaiz-ki-deen-daari-hai-ya-rabb/translation/#p-5edbd3).",
